<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
The type series was collected from mosses at 1200 m elevation on the Mont Aorai ridge. Subsequently, two individuals were extracted through the use of pyrethrin fog from moss growing on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Metrosideros" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Metrosideros" order="Myrtales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Metrosideros</taxonomicName>
. This second collecting event occurred at 1210 m elevation on Aorai.
</paragraph>
